firefox.notes: Starting with Firefox 5.0, getImageData now correctly accepts rectangles that extend beyond the bounds of the canvas; pixels outside the canvas are returned as transparent black and now also returns at least one pixel's worth of image data if a rectangle smaller than one pixel is specified.
